The**Order Placed**trigger initiates a flow when a customer completes a purchase by placing an order.

<Note>
  **Note:** This Trigger is a part of
  [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce)
  Integration
</Note>

**Topics Covered:**

- [How to Configure Order Placed Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780146915609-Order-Placed#h_01J8H4X3443S3X3G6ZXNSK1YGG)

- [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780146915609-Order-Placed#h_01J8H62GY8AYS8ZR6K9Y4ZNA10)

### How to Configure Order Placed Trigger

- While creating a Trigger Based Flow select**Order Placed**trigger.

![](./Order Placed – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)

- When setting up the**Order Placed**trigger, you will need to configure the following:
  **\*Name:**Provide a clear name for the trigger.
  **\*Description:**Explain the trigger's purpose.
  **\*Select Store:**Choose the**BigCommerce**store where the Order Placed event is being tracked.
  **\*Contact:**Define any customer-related properties that should match before activating the flow.
  **\*BigCommerce:**Specify conditions related to the order that should trigger the flow.

- Hit the**Save**button to save the configuration and start making the flow.

![](./Order Placed – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)
